@page "/getting-started"

<PageTitle>Getting Started - Vibe.UI</PageTitle>

<div class="docs-page">
    <header class="page-header">
        <h1>Getting Started</h1>
        <p class="lead">Learn how to get started with Vibe.UI in your Blazor project</p>
    </header>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>.NET 9.0 SDK or later</li>
            <li>Basic knowledge of Blazor and C#</li>
            <li>A Blazor WebAssembly or Blazor Server project</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Installation Methods</h2>
        <p>Vibe.UI offers two installation approaches to fit your workflow:</p>

        <div class="method-comparison">
            <div class="method-card">
                <h3>üõ†Ô∏è CLI Approach (Recommended)</h3>
                <p>Copy component source code directly to your project for full control and customization.</p>
                <div class="pros-cons">
                    <div class="pros">
                        <strong>Pros:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Full source code ownership</li>
                            <li>Customize any component</li>
                            <li>No package dependencies</li>
                            <li>shadcn/ui style workflow</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Projects that need component customization or want to avoid package dependencies</p>
                <a href="@GetUrl("installation")" class="btn btn-primary">View CLI Installation ‚Üí</a>
            </div>

            <div class="method-card">
                <h3>üì¶ NuGet Package</h3>
                <p>Traditional package reference for quick setup and automatic updates.</p>
                <div class="pros-cons">
                    <div class="pros">
                        <strong>Pros:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Quick installation</li>
                            <li>Automatic updates</li>
                            <li>Smaller project files</li>
                            <li>Standard .NET workflow</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Projects that prefer package management or need rapid prototyping</p>
                <a href="@GetUrl("installation")" class="btn btn-secondary">View Package Installation ‚Üí</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Quick Start (CLI)</h2>
        <p>Get started in 3 simple steps:</p>

        <div class="step-list">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h3>Install the CLI Tool</h3>
                    <CodeBlock Code="@InstallCliCode" Language="bash" />
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h3>Initialize in Your Project</h3>
                    <CodeBlock Code="@InitProjectCode" Language="bash" />
                    <p>This copies the required infrastructure files to your project.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h3>Add Components</h3>
                    <CodeBlock Code="@AddComponentsCode" Language="bash" />
                    <p>Components are copied to <code>Components/vibe/</code> directory.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Project Structure</h2>
        <p>After running <code>vibe init</code> and adding components, your project will look like:</p>
        <CodeBlock Code="@ProjectStructureCode" Language="plaintext" />
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Your First Component</h2>
        <p>Once you've added a component, use it in your Razor pages:</p>
        <CodeBlock Code="@FirstComponentCode" Language="razor" />
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Theming</h2>
        <p>Vibe.UI includes a built-in theming system with dark mode support. Components automatically adapt to the active theme.</p>
        <p>Learn more about customizing themes in the <a href="@GetUrl("theming")">Theming documentation</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Next Steps</h2>
        <div class="next-steps-grid">
            <a href="@GetUrl("installation")" class="next-step-card">
                <h3>üì¶ Installation Guide</h3>
                <p>Detailed installation instructions for both CLI and Package approaches</p>
            </a>
            <a href="@GetUrl("cli")" class="next-step-card">
                <h3>üõ†Ô∏è CLI Reference</h3>
                <p>Complete CLI command reference and usage examples</p>
            </a>
            <a href="@GetUrl("components/button")" class="next-step-card">
                <h3>üé® Browse Components</h3>
                <p>Explore all 93+ available components with live examples</p>
            </a>
            <a href="@GetUrl("theming")" class="next-step-card">
                <h3>üé≠ Theming</h3>
                <p>Customize colors, fonts, and create custom themes</p>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>

